# GIT access

Allegro's source code is maintained in a GIT repository. 
You can get clients for most platforms at <http://git-scm.com>, and there
is good documentation like the [Reference Manual](http://git-scm.com/docs).

The read-only URL is:

    git://alleg.git.sourceforge.net/gitroot/alleg/allegro

For developers with a SourceForge USERNAME it is:

    ssh://USERNAME@alleg.git.sourceforge.net/gitroot/alleg/allegro

By default you will be on the 5.1 branch. You can change the branch from
your working tree like this:

    git checkout 5.0

    git checkout 4.4

    git checkout 5.1

## Web Interface

You can browse the source code online at
<http://alleg.git.sourceforge.net/git/gitweb-index.cgi>.

## Test results

Daily test results can be seen here: <http://allegro5.org>

## Upstream tracker

Shallow test results from the Upstream Tracker:
<http://linuxtesting.org/upstream-tracker/versions/allegro.html>

## Changelogs of the GIT tree

The GIT repository also has a commit hook for [CIA], a system for tracking
open-source projects in real-time. The CIA web interface provides an RSS feed
and notifications in the `#commits` channel on the [Freenode] IRC network. You
can monitor Allegro activity at <http://cia.vc/stats/project/alleg>.

[CIA]:	    http://cia.vc/
[Freenode]: http://freenode.org/
